Liliane Bettencourt case: Fran<0xC3><0xA7>ois-Marie Banier will be tried for abuse of weakness
The court of Nanterre decided on Friday to judge the artist Fran<0xC3><0xA7>ois-Marie Banier in order to determine, as accused by the daughter of the billionaire Liliane Bettencourt, he took advantage of a state of weakness of the eighty-year-old to rob her of a part of her fortune.
The 62-year-old photographer, known for his photographs of stars, will be tried on 15 and 16 April 2010 for abuse of weakness, a crime punishable by a maximum sentence of three years imprisonment and a fine of 375,000 euros.
