This is excellent news ... The expertise will show that he (Mr. Banier) manipulated this elderly lady that we have to protect, he said.
For the past two years, Liliane Bettencourt’s only daughter has been prosecuting Fran<0xC3><0xA7>ois-Marie Banier, a photographer and artist who she accuses of taking advantage of her mother’s weakness for years to obtain a billion euros in donations, in the form of cheques, life insurance contracts or master paintings.
For her part, Liliane Bettencourt has always refuted being manipulated by the photographer, whom she considers a long-time friend.
While the court was due to examine the admissibility of Ms. Bettencourt-Meyers' lawsuit, lawyers' pleas sometimes turned to the large family unpacking on Friday.
Thus, Liliane Bettencourt’s lawyer reported three letters sent by her client (in 1999, 2003 and 2005) to her notary, in which she said she was suspicious of the husband of Fran<0xC3><0xA7>oise Bettencourt-Meyers.
