Obama “made the right speech,” the New York Times said, deeming it “both dark and uplifting.”
Roadsters: Three marathons for an agreement that saves Christmas supplies
After three sessions of marathon negotiations, the road trade unions and TLF, the only employers' organisation to remain until the end, reached an agreement on Friday night that ended the slogan of strike and the threat to Christmas supplies.
